snippet: A wave of car bombs rocked commercial streets in Baghdad on Tuesday, part of a series of attacks across the country that left 31 victims and 4 attackers dead.
abstract: Wave of car bombs rocks commercial streets in Baghdad, part of series of attacks across country that left 31 victims and 4 attackers dead; bombings are believed to have been carried out by Sunnis aiming to undermine confidence in Shiite-led government.
lead_paragraph: A wave of car bombs rocked commercial streets in Baghdad on Tuesday, part of a series of attacks across the country that left 31 victims and 4 attackers dead.

headline.main: Iraq: 35 Die in Latest Round of Attacks
